main event: An observation of a fast-moving object at an altitude of about 10,000 feet was made on October 7, 1956, in Denver, Colorado.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 20 seconds,The sighting noted a zig-zag movement before the object disappeared,The report suggested it was probably a balloon or aircraft,The object was located to the west-southeast of the observer,The visibility was clear and calm at the time of the observation.
sighted object: one fast-moving object in the sky
